<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ex Guildees Revolt.  News at 9</span><hr size=1> Norrath -- Lor Mani officials have decided not to hold back after a public flogging at a meeting hosted by former LM Guildees.<br>
<br>
&quot;We've been trying to take the high road here, trying not to say things that will make the situation less resolvable,&quot; said Fallbala Fronkensteeen, Lor Mani public relations director the day after the 15 dissident Guildees told a gathering of 200 that Lor Mani policies threaten quality of life here.<br>
<br>
&quot;But some of the things they've been saying are flat out lies, and they know it,&quot; Fronkensteeen said.<br>
<br>
&quot;The reason seems to be money. They want more money and they're willing to impose loot cost increases on the community.&quot;<br>
<br>
At a Thursday night meeting the Ex Guildees of Lor Mani group reiterated their claims that monopolistic Lor Mani practices and low fees paid to guildees are driving talent out of Lor Mani to surrounding guilds that pay more.<br>
<br>
The group resigned Lor Mani's Loot panels May 22 after negotiations for a 38 percent fee increase broke down.<br>
<br>
The management, during the presentation led by the group's president, said only Vis Maior and Wraith pay Guildees more.<br>
<br>
Ex Guildees have seen their loot stay flat or decrease the last nine years while Lor Mani &quot;management&quot; profits soar, others said to sporadic applause from the crowd dominated by ex guildees and their lack lustre hooligan friends.<br>
<br>
If it had the tone of a pep rally, you can be sure that Guilds and their leaders weren't there, said Rennhelm Haus, a Moonlight Crusaders acting president.<br>
<br>
Controlling Phat L3wtz cost are difficult enough, he said. We need the cooperation of under guildees to control costs, and I say just control, since they are rising.<br>
<br>
Lor Mani has raised fees to guildees by 8 percent over the past two years, Haus said, but it is true fees have flattened and that's a function of managed adventuring.<br>
<br>
The market tells us that it was appropriate for it to be flat for a time. But our fees are in line with other managed adventure markets. Managed adventuring is the issue.<br>
<br>
The guilds the ex guildees keep pointing to amount to an unfair comparison, haus said, because they don't have the high amount of managed adventuring like us not so uber and more family oriented large adventuring facilities, with 90 percent of the population enrolled in some form of loot plan and hidden ninja agendas.<br>
<br>
One of the highlights of the &quot;pep rally&quot; was the claim that, as of Tuesday, Vis Maior pays 307 percent more to the guildees in their guild than management pays guildees in Lor Mani.<br>
<br>
We checked into it, Fronkensteeen said. We found out it was a payment dispersal error.<br>
<br>
We would never tolerate a difference like that in a payment schedule, Fronkensteeen said. If there's a mistake, we'll rectify it. It's not our intent to pay dramatically higher loots in management than we do in these lesser beings.  And then he mumbled something and coughed a couple times.<br>
<br>
As to guildees departing, Thursday night they said three guildees have left in the last year and in the last five years, six have retired. Five have come and gone in the last 10 years.<br>
<br>
The difficulties of recruiting replacements because of Lor Mani amounts to a looming phat loot crisis, they said, considering the number of guildees now close to retirement age.<br>
<br>
Lor Mani officials countered that of the 13 guildees in, five arrived within the last four years. They count five retirees and say all have been replaced.<br>
<br>
No enchanter or inkie necro has left Lor Mani for Vis Maior, Wraith or Lotus Cult in the last 5 years, according to an Lor Mani press release.<br>
<br>
One ex guildee said to applause at Thursday night's Lor Mani bashing said, A culture has developed in Lor Mani where there are administrators who seem to think they are so benevolent and all powerful they can do it all.  Buncha hipocrytic bastards and dicknecks.<br>
<br>
And the Guildees are dispensable. Their culture doesn't respect us. It's not just the money. I don't want to support them anymore so they can continue to say at their national meetings how great they are at our expense.<br>
<br>
But Fallbala said, With their misleading and blatantly untrue statements, they are not going to develop a following among other guilds, they might get lucky and find other losers like them at the bazaar or someone fighting a seagul in the back of the Fish N' Grub for scraps, but not quality people like we are.<br>
<br>
One of the sponsors of Thursday night's meeting said, This is becoming a testosterone battle. They feel they have to put this renegade group of guildees down.<br>
<br>
